Boil a large #pot of salted water for the rice.

When boiling, add the @rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve and pop back in the #pot.

Cover with a #lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat (no oil).

Once the #pan is hot, add the @Irish Beef Mince{250%grams} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat and its packaging. Use a #spoon to break it up as it cooks.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(chopped) into small pieces.

Once the mince has browned, add the onion (with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} if necessary). Fry until it's starting to soften, ~{3-4%mins}.

Finely chop the @chilli{1}(finely chopped).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%pack} in a #sieve.

Once the onion has softened, add the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and chilli (use less if you don't like spice) to the #pan. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%min}.

Add @water{100%ml}, @passata{1%pack}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and lentils to the #pan.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Stir together. Simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%mins}. IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs loosening.

Add the @baby spinach{60%grams} a handful at a time.

Cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%mins}.

Taste and add more salt and pepper if desired.

Divide the rice between your bowls.

Top with the curry and a dollop of @yoghurt{75%grams}.